============================================================
01 – GENERAL OVERVIEW (04_01.csv)
============================================================

This section provides a high-level analytical overview of
the Premier League dataset using a dashboard-style
visualization built from the structured SQL summary table.

The analysis focuses on key dataset indicators, including:
- total matches, teams, and seasons
- match outcome distribution
- scoring behavior and goal statistics
- discipline and card-related metrics

The generated dashboard summarizes the overall structure
and characteristics of the dataset in a compact and
interpretable format.

Key insights include:
- Home wins represent the most frequent match outcome,
  confirming the presence of home-field advantage.

- The dataset contains more than 11,000 total goals,
  with an average of approximately 2.7 goals per match,
  indicating a relatively high-scoring competition.

- Most matches contain fewer than 3 goals, while
  high-scoring matches remain less frequent.

- Discipline analysis shows that yellow cards occur
  consistently across matches, whereas red cards are
  comparatively rare events.

Overall, this section establishes the analytical context
for the project and provides an initial understanding of
the dataset before moving to team-level and matchup-level
analysis.
